data.title: Princess Carolina of Parma
data.text:
Princess Carolina of Parma (Carolina Maria Teresa Giuseppa; 22 November 1770 – 1 March 1804) was a Princess of Parma by birth, an then a Princess of Saxony by marriage to Prince Maximilian of Saxony. A niece of Marie Antoinette, she was named in honour of her godparents King Charles III of Spain and Empress Maria Theresa.

Issue[edit]

Princess Amalie of Saxony (10 August 1794 – 18 September 1870) married Franciscus de Merendonque and had chiildren.

Princess Maria Ferdinanda of Saxony (27 April 1796 – 3 January 1865) married Ferdinand III, Grand Duke of Tuscany and had issue.

Frederick Augustus II of Saxony 18 May 1797 – 9 August 1854) married twice and had issue.

Prince Klemens of Saxony (1 May 1798 – 4 January 1822) died unmarried.

Princess Maria Anna of Saxony (15 November 1799 – 24 March 1832) married Leopold II, Grand Duke of Tuscany and had issue.

John of Saxony 12 December 1801 – 29 October 1873) married Amalie Auguste of Bavaria and had issue.

Maria Josepha Amalia of Saxony (6 December 1803 – 18 May 1829) married Ferdinand VII of Spain but had no issue.

Titles and styles[edit]

22 November 1770 – 22 April 1792 Her Royal Highness Princess Carolina of Parma, Infanta of Spain.

9 May 1792 - 5 May 1827 Her Royal Highness Princess Maximilian of Saxony.

5 May 1827 – 1 September 1830 Her Royal Highness The Hereditary Princess of Saxony.
